-- Fed Sells $8.603 Billion of Treasuries in Second Operation
-- B y   L i z   C a p o   M c C o r m i c k
-- 2012-02-08T19:04:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/fed-sells-8-603-billion-of-treasuries-in-second-operation.html
The  Federal Reserve  sold $8.603
billion in  Treasury securities  maturing in less than one year as
part of its plan to lower borrowing costs that’s become known as
Operation Twist.  The central bank sold debt maturing from June 2013 to
November 2013 in its second open-market operation of the day,
according to the Federal Reserve Bank of New York’s  website .
Federal Reserve Bank of New York statement today. It purchased
$1.813 billion of notes due in 2036 to 2041 earlier.  The Fed is replacing $400 billion of short-term debt in its
portfolio with longer-term Treasuries in an effort to reduce
borrowing costs further and counter rising risks of a recession.  To contact the reporter on this story:
